content.detailedDescription:
I was driving to the grocery store.  i saw a light in the sky that at first i thought was an airplane, then i noticed there were 2 lights.  it kind of looked like 2 airplanes, kind of.  it isn't very far at all to the grocery store.  as i approached the parking lot, it was apparent to me that these weren't airplanes.  they hadn't really moved much and were looking bigger and brighter.  i parked my car in the grocery store parking lot, facing the lights in the sky.  the lights were much larger and brighter at this point, i had to film it, because i couldn't figure out what they were. the light on the right appeared to be pulsating, getting bigger, smaller, like it was changing size/shape. i made a quick video of it and then decided to take pics.  i tried zooming in when i took the pics.  i clicked repeatedly.  what the ?   no way!  i think i'm hallucinating.  
so bizarre.  the one pic shows the light on the right just before it disappeared (it looks laike a little gray shape).  the light on the left, just hung around for a few minutes more and then went off to the left, and to me, it looks like it starts flashing (like n airplane, maybe it's just me?)and then gone.  i was excited to think i may have actually finally seen an unknown object.
content.summary: Video'd lights, one looked like pulsing big/small, took pics, you tell me please

content.detailedDescription: On a fishing trip at touchwood lake in the lakeland provincial rec. area in alberta east of lac la biche two friends and i were heading to camp and admiring the night sky which was very clear that night. i spotted a light that was like a satellite or iss but didn't move across the sky, it remained stationary while the light itself flashed. one friend pointed out that it seemed more like a lighthouse than a flashing beacon, the light didn't flash it seemed to dim out and in as if it were rotating. after a few seconds of watching this thing a few smaller red lights started to appear distant from the first light but all 'flowing' toward it and disappearing when getting close to it as if being absorbed. we watched this for a few more seconds and then headed back to camp realizing that we had nothing with us to take a decent photo or video. much of the rest of the night around the fire was spend discussing what we just saw and joking that the invasion had begun.
content.summary: Stationary lighthouse like light in atmosphere absorbs smaller red lights.

content.detailedDescription:
Driving east towards scarborough along a170 on a clear frosty morning (08:56 29.11.16) having turned out of seamer moor lane i saw what appeared to be 4 short, distinct contrails at altitude which included tight turns the northernmost appeared to contain a triangular tight 170 degree movement with an aircraft / craft moving quickly east over the scarborough south bay.  each contrail abruptly stopped, they were horizontal to each other in aspect and whilst i had noted a craft moving east at the end of the northernmost tip of the last contrail within a second it was no longer visible and the contrail abruptly stopped being formed.  all 4 short, distinct contrails were recorded for 15 seconds by the dashcam of my vehicle.  i was unable to stop and take more detailed images.  as i drove on i negotiated a corner and lost sight of the trails for a matter of seconds.  i began to descended a hill, looking east at the first break in tree line i saw the 4 contrails had already begun to disintegrate and there was no sign of any recognisable aircraft or any other contrails being formed.

i am aware this area is subject to military flights and training but i have never witnessed military aircraft making such manoeuvres or creating short contrails.
content.summary: Witnessed 4 distinct tight contrails not linked with tight turns and one craft moving east from the northernmost trail.  unable to stop but 15 seconds of video on hd dashcam

content.detailedDescription:
Large triangular craft with 5 pinkish glowing lites = approx 20 seconds

at approximately 12:30 am on september 22nd, 2014, i stepped out on the rear deck for some night air. i noticed 2 lights in the sky approaching from the north in a straight southerly direction. as the craft approached i was able to see a total of 5 lights that were swirling glowing pinkish white inside the domes of the light enclosures - 2 on each wing (1 @ front). the craft was a very dark metal color (charcoal) and triangular/boomerang in shape. i could even see the raised ribbing on the wings. the nose of the craft had a somewhat rounded front. as it flew directly overhead i could see that the rear of the craft was bridged wing to wing approx. a quarter of the way down the wing span. it seemed to me that viewing from inside the craft could also be done looking in the opposite direction of travel as there were viewing panels at the rear.  the craft made absolutely no sound whatsoever as it traveled directly over me and our backyard. i had a very good visual of the craft and had to lean over the deck to see the entire craft due to our covered deck portion on the south end of our home as it flew overhead across the boulevard - over the next row of houses until out of sight. the altitude of the craft was very low (a couple of hundred feet or less). it was larger than a military jet yet resembled the shape of a stealth bomber. my estimate of size is approx 100 feet wing to wing as i was directly underneath the center of it and one wing was over our backyard fence and the other would have reached past the front of our home.  what struck me the most was the silence of the craft and the lights which seemed be electro-magnetic swirling/sparking inside each housing. i did not take my eyes off the craft during the entire time, then went inside and drew a picture of what i had seen.  i continued to search the reports on the net for a very long time and continue to do so even today. and i did find someones graphic that depicts what i had seen almost identically. (attached)
content.summary: Large triangular craft with 6 pinkish glowing lites overhead

content.detailedDescription: The witness and her husband live in their own home.  on nov. 5, 2016 at about 2 pm, the witness was sitting in a chair on the front deck, which faces due southeast.  they often sit outside on this deck and watch for eagles, which are fairly common in the area. she had her back to the northwest.  she saw a shiny object that appeared to be to the east above the house at 10249 nightingale st.  it slowly moved in a westward direction and to her left.  at one point it appeared to be above the front yard tree of the next-door neighbor to the ne.  this tree is about 42 feet tall and the object appeared to be about 40 feet above it, or at an altitude of about 80 feet.  this would have been about 100 feet from the witness.  the object never paused in its steady flight until the roof of the witness’ house cut off her view of it.  the object made no sound, had no wings, left no vapor trail.  it was in sight for maybe 3 to 4 minutes.  to the best of her memory, the object was about as wide as 5 thumb widths at arm’s length. the shape of the object was unusual and unfamiliar – see witness sketch.  it could possibly be described as shaped like a double hamburger.  it had three shiny regions and two dull regions.  the husband of the witness was raking leaves in the back yard on the other side of the house and heard and saw nothing.  the witness had a cell phone with built-in camera with her but did not think of taking a picture.  also, she did not think of calling to her husband in the back yard.  the witness states that she is clairvoyant and able to read people’s minds, which she generally avoids doing, but in this case she tried to read the mind of any being in the object and came up with nothing.  just after the object passed out of sight, she had the feeling that it had turned and was moving north.  she also received the impression that the object could “collapse on itself”, that is, it was capable of folding together so that the shiny regions would hide the dull regions.  then it would have been an oval shape.
content.summary: Saw roughly oval object fly past 100 ft distant at closest

content.detailedDescription: I was returning rented movies and games to the family video on the west side of kent; when finished, i left, traveling through downtown to reach the convenient gas station on w. main. when i approached the stoplight to turn onto w. main, my gaze was, for whatever reason, pushed over the bridge to my left. immediately as i turned to look at the horizon over the bridge, an intensely colored green orb appeared, pausing briefly before rocketing southward at breakneck speed, disappearing suddenly into nothing and leaving behind a very short-lived green aura and what appeared to be sparking shrapnel, at which point, all traces of the object disappeared.
content.summary: Intense brilliant green flying object observed flying over sr59/w. main bridge while at stoplight, facing sb towards longmere dr.

content.detailedDescription: On november 26th 2016 at approximately 7 am in the morning my wife and i  decided to sit in the hot tub.  we noticed a hovering object approxiamately 3 or 4 miles a way in the sky approximately 30 degrees from horizon. it really stuck out because there were no other stars visable that morning.  we could not see the structure of the object but the red green and white flashing lites formed a triangle  it hovered and flickered flashing lites for about 30 minutes.  i got the binoculars out and thats when i noticed the triangle shape.  while i was looking at it through the binoculars it disappeared on me.  approximately one second later i then located it a good ways away from where it just was.  it had suddenly moved very fast.  it hovered for another 3 minutes in that spot then slowly faded away until i could see it no longer.  i have always scoffed at the idea of ufo's but i really dont know of any man made object that could do what i just witnessed.  we orignally tried to rationalize it away, perhaps a weather satellite, but it was to low, it seems gravity would pull it down. then we thought a drone but it couldnt possibly move that fast,could it? at any rate i kind of wish i wouldnt have seen it because i cant stop thinking about it. i did video it but it was too dark to see it good, however you can kind of see its white flashing lite
content.summary: My wife and i observed  flashing lites in the sky that formed the shape of a triangle it hovered for 30 minutes then disappeared and i spotted it a second later a long way away

content.detailedDescription: Sitting out at beach deck late on a cold night. what i thought i saw was a meteorite entering the atmosphere over the ocean but it didn't fizzle out and it got a lot closer to me. i remember in my mind as it slowed to a stop trying to eliminate anything else it could be but nothing added up to what i was witnessing. i had to focus to get as many details as i could. when it had stopped or i guess "hovered," the fire had two distinct flames underneath a transparent type oval shape above it. the oval shape had many bright orange lines going in several directions. the flames stayed somewhat upwards other than when it made its decent. the flames did waver some as if it were falling a bit or maybe the wind was blowing it but it did not go out. it then moved back out in another direction of the ocean into the sky until i couldn't see it any longer. it didn't go super fast when it left. it left slowly but must have picked up speed heading away from me as it was gone pretty quickly. i then woke up my husband freaking out. it's only been a few days but this seems to be consuming me.
content.flightPath: Stationary,Hovering then path,Straight-line path,Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: Fireball like a meteorite falling from sky but stopped and hovered. then took the shape of an oval with fire under it. translucent with many orange lines going through the oval part.

content.detailedDescription: @ 2255 hours i stepped outside for a smoke, in the ne sky, i noticed a bright redish orange hue in the sky. i sky watch on a regular basis & the location of this object was nothing i'd seen before. at first i thought it was the planet mars, given it's color, i checked my app to see if it was indeed mars or a star. the app showed mars had already set behind me relative to where i observed this object. i immediately contacted the local mufon number on the website & left a message. i originally reported the object in the southwest sky on the message i left, it was actually in the northeast sky. i observed it for about 3 minutes, in that 3 minutes, it began to get noticeably get brighter, but, no movement. i was in a state of disbelief & "this isn't real" kept going through my mind. realizing what it might be, i went into my apartment to grab the binoculars, when i came back out, it was gone (unknown direction of travel). i went back & timed how long it took me to walk inside, grab the binoculars & return back outside, that time lapse was around 35 seconds. it was nowhere to be found. i texted my brother & informed him of what i saw. the only other thing i noticed was normal air traffic coming from the east, turning south to land at john wayne airport, this was after i went inside to grab the binoculars.
content.summary: A bright redish orange hue in the nw sky hovering.
